16 hereafter permit and not to limit any redevelopment powers permitted under the
17 "Redevelopment Powers Law."
18 SECTION 2.
19 The election superintendent of the City of Cedartown shall call and conduct an election, as
20 provided in this section, for the purpose of submitting this Act to the electors of the City of
21 Cedartown for approval or rejection. The election superintendent shall conduct that election
22 on the Tuesday next following the first Monday in November, 2025, and shall issue the call
23 and conduct that election as provided by general law. The election superintendent shall
24 cause the date and purpose of the election to be published once at least 90 days immediately
25 preceding the date thereof and once a week for two weeks immediately preceding the date
26 thereof in the official organ of Polk County, Georgia. The ballot shall have written or printed
27 thereon the words:
28 "( ) YES Shall the Act be approved which authorizes the City of Cedartown, Georgia,
29 ( ) NO to exercise all redevelopment powers allowed under the 'Redevelopment
30 Powers Law,' as it may be amended from time to time?"
31 All persons desiring to vote for approval of the Act shall vote "Yes," and all persons desiring
32 to vote for rejection of the Act shall vote "No." If more than one-half of the votes cast on
33 such question are for approval of the Act, then Section 1 of this Act shall become of full
34 force and effect immediately. If this Act is not so approved or if the election is not
35 conducted as provided in this section, Section 1 of this Act shall not become effective and
36 this Act shall be automatically repealed on the first day of January immediately following
37 such election date. The expense of such election shall be borne by the City of Cedartown.
38 It shall be the election superintendent's duty to certify the result thereof to the Secretary of
39 State.
